<br>
If you havent done HHH before please come an hour early and start a halfling warrior or rogue and meet Myriah in Rivervale. She will give you equipment and intructions. You will then have time to level a bit before the others log on. You could also start a hobbit earlier in the week and send me a tell and we can get you going sooner. It would be nice to get your Hoard Hobbit to 5th level as some HHH members are 8th now.<br>
<br>
Myriah Ebon Goddess, 56th Enchanter and Hobbit Shepherdess. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uclemmsmitson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>clemmsmitson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(7/24/01 3:22:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=168.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HHH Six: Bashing in Black Borrow Aug5 2pm EDT (2000CET)</span><hr size=1> Ill bring my twinked out cleric halfling, Im sure she could out damage some warriors anyways!<br>
